lyrics.stanza:
Though we are often swayed and tossed,
Changeless forever He endures;
None of His promises are lost;
None is so sure in heav'n or earth.

Though we are fickle, change our mind,
He'll ne'er forsake us, never leave;
Even when spurned, He draws us nigh;
No earthly friend's as true as He.

Lord, when such faithful love we see,
Loudly we praise with heart and voice;
Stronger than death, steadfast than seas;
Melted, our hearts admire, rejoice!
